The countries which make up the African Elephant Coalition (AEC) submitted five proposals to CITES which call for a ban on the ivory trade.

The AEC said in a statement, the ban would include "the closure of domestic ivory markets, the destruction of ivory stockpiles, ending the Decision-Making Mechanism for legalising trade in ivory, and limiting the export of wild, live African elephants to conservation projects in their natural habitat".

